The paper deals with a decomposition theory that is inspired by modular graph decomposition, but is applicable to structures beyond graphs. This suggests that the paper may belong to categories related to data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses algorithmic tools and efficiency, which are common themes in computational geometry (cs.CG), computational complexity (cs.CC), and graph theory (cs.GT).
